@kaijianding i see, thanks for the detailed explanation. actually, to the best of my knowledge, none of the druid ingestions use interval start time as segment version and new segments always have higher versions. i'm not sure what else breaks down when that assumption is taken away.

That said, IntervalStartVersioningPolicy does exist in the code and I'm not sure when it would be used. if we do want to make the update then, I think, VersionedIntervalTimeline should be modified to handle the case of overlapping segments with same version.

does anyone else have an opinion ?

@drcrallen 
clock skew between druid nodes and hdfs nodes might end up deleting unintended logs, I will note that in the documentation.

regarding ovelord and coordinator merge, helper stuff introduced here is already in an extensible form.
